  "prompt": "Do all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE?",
  "response": "Not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE). While most modern smartphones released in the last decade are equipped with Bluetooth 4.0 or higher, older models may have earlier versions of Bluetooth, such as 2.1 or 3.0. \n\nBluetooth 4.0 was introduced in 2010 and brought significant improvements, including BLE, which is designed for low power consumption in devices that need to maintain a connection with minimal energy use. As of now, most smartphones on the market typically support Bluetooth 4.0 or newer versions (like 4.1, 4.2, 5.0, and so on).\n\nIf you are considering a specific model, it's best to check its specifications to confirm the version of Bluetooth it supports.",
